                            <comment id="482009" author="sebastien" created="Mon, 22 Dec 2025 08:51:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The error comes from this code that is called in sanity-sec test_43 cleanup (&lt;tt&gt;cleanup_for_enc_tests&lt;/tt&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;tt&gt;remount_client_normally&lt;/tt&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;tt&gt;remove_enc_key&lt;/tt&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;remove_enc_key() {
	local dummy_key

	$LCTL set_param -n ldlm.namespaces.*.lru_size=clear        &amp;lt;----------- -ENOENT
	sync ; echo 3 &amp;gt; /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
	dummy_key=$(keyctl show | awk &apos;$7 ~ &quot;^fscrypt:&quot; {print $1}&apos;)
	if [ -n &quot;$dummy_key&quot; ]; then
		keyctl revoke $dummy_key
		keyctl reap
	fi
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first occurrence of &apos;test_43 returned 2&apos; I could find dates back from 2025-10-04. It does not correspond to any significant change in this cleanup code. So it looks like we can end up with &apos;leftovers&apos; under /sys/fs/lustre/ldlm/namespaces/ after unmounting then remounting clients. Not sure where this is coming from, but to avoid failing tests because of that I have pushed patch &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19449&quot; title=&quot;sanity-sec test_43: test_43 returned 2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19449&quot;&gt;LU-19449&lt;/a&gt; tests: ignore lru_size error in test cleanup&quot; at &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/63135&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/63135&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
